# Screen Spec Format

Each screen is a `*.screen.json` file in `spec/screens/`. The compiler reads these to generate React components.

## Top-Level Structure

```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "route": "/dashboard",
  "meta": { "title": "Dashboard", "description": "Main dashboard" },
  "tree": { /* root node */ }
}
```

- `version` — always 1
- `route` — URL path for the generated page
- `tree` — the root node of the screen (always a container type)

## Node Structure

Every node has this shape:

```json
{
  "id": "unique_id",
  "type": "Stack",
  "name": "Hero Section",
  "props": { },
  "style": { },
  "children": [ /* child nodes */ ]
}
```

- `id` — unique within the screen (e.g. `"stack_abc123"`)
- `type` — one of the built-in types (see below)
- `name` — human-readable label shown in the layers panel
- `props` — type-specific properties
- `style` — visual styling (see NodeStyle below)
- `children` — nested child nodes (omit for leaf nodes)

## Built-In Node Types

**Layout:** Stack, Grid, Section, ScrollArea, Box, Container, AspectRatio, Frame
**Content:** Heading, Text, Image, Link, Divider, List, Icon, SVG, Video, Embed, Blockquote, Code
**Form:** Input, Textarea, Select, Checkbox, RadioGroup, Switch, Slider, Label, FileUpload, Button, Form
**Display:** Card, Badge, Avatar, Tooltip, Progress, Skeleton, Alert, Accordion, Carousel, Calendar
**Overlay:** Modal, Dialog, Drawer, Sheet, Popover, HoverCard, DropdownMenu
**Navigation:** Nav, Breadcrumb, Pagination, Stepper, Sidebar, AppBar, Tabs
**Shapes:** Rectangle, Ellipse, Line

**Component types:**
- `ComponentInstance` — instance of a DS component (importPath, componentName, componentProps)
- `ComponentRef` — reference to a custom composite component
- `ExternalComponent` — external library component

## ComponentInstance Node

Used for design system components (shadcn, antd, MUI, etc.):

```json
{
  "id": "btn_1",
  "type": "ComponentInstance",
  "name": "Primary Button",
  "props": {
    "componentName": "Button",
    "importPath": "studio:shadcn",
    "componentProps": { "variant": "default", "label": "Submit" }
  }
}
```

## NodeStyle Properties

Style values can be raw CSS values or token references (prefixed with `$`):

```json
{
  "style": {
    "fontSize": "$typography.body.fontSize",
    "color": "$color.primary",
    "paddingTop": 16,
    "paddingBottom": 16,
    "backgroundColor": "#ffffff",
    "borderRadius": "$borderRadius.md",
    "width": "100%"
  }
}
```

**Categories:** typography (fontSize, fontWeight, lineHeight, textAlign, color), sizing (width, height, min/max variants), spacing (paddingTop/Right/Bottom/Left, marginTop/Right/Bottom/Left), background (backgroundColor, backgroundImage), border (borderWidth, borderColor, borderStyle, borderRadius), effects (opacity, boxShadow, effects array), transforms (rotation, scaleX, scaleY), layout (display, flexDirection, justifyContent, alignItems, gap, position).

## Responsive Overrides

Nodes can have breakpoint-specific style overrides:

```json
{
  "responsive": {
    "tablet": { "fontSize": 14, "paddingTop": 8 },
    "mobile": { "fontSize": 12, "flexDirection": "column" }
  }
}
```

## Interactions

Optional interaction bindings:

```json
{
  "interactions": {
    "onClick": { "action": "navigate", "target": "/about" },
    "visibleWhen": { "state": "isLoggedIn", "operator": "truthy" }
  }
}
```
